1 A RESOLUTION
2 To commend Todd Wallace for his leadership during the recovery and revitalization of the
3 Lakeview community in New Orleans following Hurricane Katrina.
4 WHEREAS, it is fitting to recognize Todd Wallace for his outstanding civic-
5 mindedness and to commend him for his leadership during the rebuilding of the Lakeview
6 neighborhood in the wake of Hurricane Katrina; and
7 WHEREAS, Mr. Wallace, a former president of the Lakeview Civic Improvement
8 Association, played a pivotal role during the recovery of Lakeview, supported numerous
9 local businesses, and fostered unity within the community following the devastation wrought
10 by Hurricane Katrina; and
11 WHEREAS, Mr. Wallace was integral to the success of the Lot Next Door Program
12 and the Lakeview-specific Phase II Property Program, both of which transformed blighted
13 lots into revitalized properties and valuable green spaces and protected property values in
14 the Lakeview neighborhood; and
15 WHEREAS, Mr. Wallace's efforts helped to maintain the integrity of Lakeview,
16 fostered responsible development, and supported the neighborhood's recovery; and
17 WHEREAS, Mr. Wallace is a founding member of the Friends of Lakeview, which
18 helped initiate the redevelopment of the New Basin Canal Park; the two-mile stretch of
19 property, which was destroyed by Hurricane Katrina, has been restored with trees, walkway
20 lanterns, and sidewalks; and
